1
00:00:02,240 --> 00:00:03,360
Her name is Lalin.

2
00:00:04,040 --> 00:00:05,240
My only daughter.

3
00:00:06,560 --> 00:00:07,760
I understand it well that,

4
00:00:08,040 --> 00:00:09,120
How does it feel...

5
00:00:10,080 --> 00:00:11,040
when we failed.

6
00:00:26,240 --> 00:00:28,160
- You cannot get inside, Lalin. - Move!

7
00:00:28,320 --> 00:00:29,640
I'm gonna a word with Arisa.

8
00:00:30,880 --> 00:00:31,840
Hey, ma'am!

9
00:00:32,040 --> 00:00:33,600
Can you please quit avoiding me?

10
00:00:40,120 --> 00:00:41,440
Let's talk for once.

11
00:00:48,240 --> 00:00:49,200
Why do you come?

12
00:00:50,280 --> 00:00:51,600
Got any more lies to use?

13
00:00:52,240 --> 00:00:53,600
How can you say it like that?

14
00:00:54,480 --> 00:00:56,320
Aren't you also the one who lie too?

15
00:01:00,120 --> 00:01:01,240
Isn't it the right choice?

16
00:01:04,320 --> 00:01:07,240
I have to protect myself from people like you.

17
00:01:08,760 --> 00:01:10,880
We are both liars.

18
00:01:11,840 --> 00:01:13,160
What do you want more?

19
00:01:13,480 --> 00:01:15,040
I didn't want to do it.

20
00:01:15,840 --> 00:01:17,320
But my mom asked me to.

21
00:01:19,360 --> 00:01:21,640
One day, I'm going to tell you the truth anyway.

22
00:01:23,520 --> 00:01:26,000
But how can I know that you are my mother's rivals?

23
00:01:30,640 --> 00:01:32,720
Perhaps you knew it all along?

24
00:01:34,440 --> 00:01:36,760
You dated me just because my mother's business?

25
00:01:43,800 --> 00:01:45,000
I don't care whatever you think.

26
00:01:45,360 --> 00:01:46,600
I just didn't have a chance to tell you...

27
00:01:47,160 --> 00:01:48,640
that I got any other job.

28
00:01:51,480 --> 00:01:53,920
But you lied about everything.

29
00:01:54,680 --> 00:01:56,160
Name. Background.

30
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:58,040
Now you're standing here.

31
00:01:59,520 --> 00:02:01,000
Does it have any truth left?

32
00:02:03,400 --> 00:02:04,800
It's my feeling.

33
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:08,640
All my feelings are real.

34
00:02:11,880 --> 00:02:13,760
Noone forced me.

35
00:02:16,960 --> 00:02:18,040
What about you?

36
00:02:20,160 --> 00:02:23,560
Have you got any feeling for me in these few months?

37
00:02:26,160 --> 00:02:27,840
My feeling doesn't matter.

38
00:02:30,160 --> 00:02:31,440
Because two of us...

39
00:02:31,960 --> 00:02:33,040
will never work.

40
00:02:35,280 --> 00:02:37,560
The relationship that starts with lies.

41
00:02:40,240 --> 00:02:41,760
There is no good ending for that.

42
00:02:47,880 --> 00:02:49,040
Every moments,

43
00:02:52,720 --> 00:02:54,760
There's nothing worth to remember.

44
00:02:56,840 --> 00:02:58,440
I'm an easy to forget person.

45
00:03:02,640 --> 00:03:03,320
Fine.

46
00:03:06,520 --> 00:03:09,600
I'll take that everything between us was never happened.

47
00:03:11,640 --> 00:03:12,760
And you...

48
00:03:13,640 --> 00:03:17,840
A stranger who I never ever know the real her.

49
00:04:22,440 --> 00:04:24,600
Left! Left! Right! Right!

50
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:29,640
Left! Left! Right! Right! Kick! Kick!

51
00:04:30,680 --> 00:04:32,840
Left! Left! Right! Right!

52
00:04:38,040 --> 00:04:39,680
We better take a break, miss.

53
00:04:45,720 --> 00:04:47,120
We practiced for hours.

54
00:04:57,960 --> 00:05:02,640
You're upset that Lyla is Lalin, your rival's daughter, aren't you?

55
00:05:10,320 --> 00:05:11,920
You don't have to worry.

56
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:14,040
I broke up with her.

57
00:05:15,040 --> 00:05:16,720
And I haven't take her seriously.

58
00:05:21,440 --> 00:05:22,200
Miss.

59
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:26,520
Don't you really have any feelings for Weiling's daughter?

60
00:05:35,280 --> 00:05:36,040
No, I don't.

61
00:05:39,240 --> 00:05:41,200
The revenge for my father and mother...

62
00:05:42,160 --> 00:05:43,640
is the most important thing.

63
00:05:53,400 --> 00:05:54,440
Let's continue.

64
00:05:57,480 --> 00:05:59,120
Yes, miss. Come on!

65
00:06:00,680 --> 00:06:02,840
Left! Left! Right! Right!

66
00:06:05,680 --> 00:06:06,640
That's not very easy.

67
00:06:07,480 --> 00:06:11,320
You know that me and Weiling are a long time partner.

68
00:06:11,480 --> 00:06:14,560
We know each other well so the workflow is very good.

69
00:06:17,240 --> 00:06:19,040
But if you don't try anything new,

70
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:22,520
you still stick to the same result.

71
00:06:23,040 --> 00:06:25,680
Maybe going off the old track,

72
00:06:26,320 --> 00:06:28,640
it also makes the market moving.

73
00:06:31,480 --> 00:06:35,760
"Trust" is not the easy thing people can gain.

74
00:06:36,360 --> 00:06:37,840
It needs time.

75
00:06:39,160 --> 00:06:43,680
I'd say you need more flight time in the job,

76
00:06:43,720 --> 00:06:46,760
if you really want to be in this business.

77
00:06:48,240 --> 00:06:49,880
Look at how Weiling counterplay...

78
00:06:51,520 --> 00:06:54,640
You might got a lot of money and won the aunction.

79
00:06:55,280 --> 00:07:01,080
But she came to my mother and my mother forced me to choose her.

80
00:07:04,680 --> 00:07:06,040
Understood.

81
00:07:07,640 --> 00:07:10,480
That you don't enough power.

82
00:07:11,400 --> 00:07:13,280
So you have to follow your mother.

83
00:07:20,160 --> 00:07:23,960
I'd like to give you some advice as a long time businessman.

84
00:07:25,360 --> 00:07:30,040
You can use this advice to other businessman.

85
00:07:32,560 --> 00:07:34,360
You can't just use your guts.

86
00:07:35,640 --> 00:07:39,400
You need look inside your target's hearts.

87
00:07:40,720 --> 00:07:44,920
Thank you for the business advice.

88
00:07:45,880 --> 00:07:50,360
Maybe I need new techniques just to satisfy you.

89
00:07:52,080 --> 00:07:54,160
I'm not a complex man.

90
00:07:54,840 --> 00:07:56,040
Easy to satisfy.

91
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:58,880
You just need to hit the right spot.

92
00:08:11,560 --> 00:08:13,440
- Hello, sir. - Hello.

93
00:08:22,320 --> 00:08:23,760
You guys saw that girl there?

94
00:08:24,400 --> 00:08:26,120
Her schedule always full.

95
00:08:40,640 --> 00:08:41,400
Not enough?

96
00:08:41,880 --> 00:08:44,000
I ain't cleaning your mess if you puke.

97
00:08:45,240 --> 00:08:46,000
No!

98
00:08:46,480 --> 00:08:50,200
I will drink it all up so I can forget everything.

99
00:08:50,640 --> 00:08:54,760
Those liquors just a temporary things. When you sober, you will still remember everything.

100
00:08:55,280 --> 00:08:59,720
Then I'll drink everyday so I can forget everyday.

101
00:09:00,760 --> 00:09:01,480
Damn girl.

102
00:09:02,360 --> 00:09:04,240
What do you want me to do then?

103
00:09:04,880 --> 00:09:08,760
Do you want me to think like all these months are just my imagination?

104
00:09:09,440 --> 00:09:11,160
Didn't you lie to her too?

105
00:09:14,560 --> 00:09:18,440
Come on. You know that you and her is impossible.

106
00:09:18,440 --> 00:09:22,760
Is it better to just focus on being heir of your mom's business?

107
00:09:24,680 --> 00:09:25,760
You know what?

108
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:30,040
My knowledge about this business is on negative level.

109
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:35,200
In the meeting room, I understand nothing at all.

110
00:09:37,080 --> 00:09:41,960
Can't do whatever I want and my love is just a lie!

111
00:09:42,160 --> 00:09:43,800
What do I have left in my life?

112
00:09:45,240 --> 00:09:46,240
Obviously me.

113
00:09:46,360 --> 00:09:48,200
I still got your back, Lalin.

114
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:51,480
At least I still got a friend like you.

115
00:09:51,520 --> 00:09:52,640
Everything will be alright.

116
00:10:00,320 --> 00:10:00,820
Lalin.

117
00:10:02,640 --> 00:10:03,800
Can we talk?

118
00:10:03,920 --> 00:10:05,200
About what?

119
00:10:05,680 --> 00:10:07,360
Imma drink with my friend.

120
00:10:10,560 --> 00:10:11,600
Let's just talk.

121
00:10:13,960 --> 00:10:14,960
Just the two of us.

122
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:29,200
What do you want, miss Arisa?

123
00:10:29,760 --> 00:10:31,600
CEO of A-list company.

124
00:10:39,080 --> 00:10:41,920
If there's nothing, I'll excuse myself.

125
00:10:42,360 --> 00:10:43,680
My time is precious.

126
00:11:03,600 --> 00:11:06,680
Drink too much? Your body's hot.

127
00:11:08,480 --> 00:11:09,880
You don't have to worry about me.

128
00:11:10,560 --> 00:11:11,920
I can take care of myself.

129
00:11:13,840 --> 00:11:14,640
Lalin.

130
00:11:16,240 --> 00:11:17,880
Can we go back like we used to?

131
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:20,760
Hold on.

132
00:11:22,280 --> 00:11:24,520
Days ago, you just broke up with me.

133
00:11:25,280 --> 00:11:26,680
But now you wanna make up.

134
00:11:28,840 --> 00:11:30,240
Why suddenly the hot and cold?

135
00:11:32,440 --> 00:11:33,000
Lalin...

136
00:11:36,240 --> 00:11:39,240
People just need some time to learn about their feeling.

137
00:11:40,880 --> 00:11:43,200
We both got our own reason to lie.

138
00:11:57,320 --> 00:11:59,920
Today, I cannot lie to my own feeling anymore.

139
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:05,400
Everything we've been through is nice, really nice.

140
00:12:07,240 --> 00:12:09,000
So nice I don't want to lose it.

141
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:17,840
Please give me a chance.

142
00:12:22,440 --> 00:12:24,960
I promised I'll never make you cry again.

143
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:36,840
From now on, no more lies to each other.

144
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:46,000
Thank you.

145
00:13:02,960 --> 00:13:05,400
I think you should give it a second thought.

146
00:13:05,880 --> 00:13:09,680
This might be our chance to use Weiling's close ones as a weapon.

147
00:13:10,520 --> 00:13:13,840
Our target got inside our lair, why let it go so easier?

148
00:13:40,674 --> 00:13:43,108
Hey, What are you doing here?!

149
00:13:43,841 --> 00:13:45,108
Stalking me?

150
00:13:45,541 --> 00:13:46,541
What?

151
00:13:47,008 --> 00:13:48,341
Drunk again?

152
00:13:49,174 --> 00:13:50,474
I live here.

153
00:13:54,808 --> 00:13:55,908
Ok. Ok.

154
00:13:56,308 --> 00:13:57,674
Thought you were some psycho.

155
00:14:02,441 --> 00:14:03,674
Those bottles.

156
00:14:04,241 --> 00:14:06,174
Wanna be a living legend?

157
00:14:07,241 --> 00:14:08,908
You are such an alcoholic.

158
00:14:10,241 --> 00:14:12,841
Right, miss Somsak, please stop.

159
00:14:13,408 --> 00:14:15,674
No more getting the fuel and park the car today?

160
00:14:21,341 --> 00:14:22,074
You.

161
00:14:23,974 --> 00:14:26,041
- Here. Let me help. - No need to.

162
00:14:26,508 --> 00:14:27,441
I'll help myself.

163
00:14:33,874 --> 00:14:35,541
Come on. I'll help.

164
00:14:40,174 --> 00:14:42,074
Now you owe me nothing.

165
00:14:49,708 --> 00:14:51,641
I'm not going back to help you taking out the trash.

166
00:14:52,941 --> 00:14:54,941
No need to help me. I'll take care of it.

167
00:14:55,241 --> 00:14:56,541
Worry about yourself.

168
00:15:03,608 --> 00:15:04,541
Where can I put them down?

169
00:15:04,774 --> 00:15:05,941
Anywhere that you can.

170
00:15:28,608 --> 00:15:29,108
Hey.

171
00:15:31,408 --> 00:15:32,174
I'll take my leave.

172
00:15:32,441 --> 00:15:33,308
Wait. Where're you going?

173
00:15:33,841 --> 00:15:34,708
Taking out the trash.

174
00:15:35,808 --> 00:15:36,974
I just want to say thank you.

175
00:15:37,041 --> 00:15:38,008
Oh, you're welcome.

176
00:15:38,241 --> 00:15:38,808
See ya.

177
00:16:14,308 --> 00:16:15,408
Woke up, love?

178
00:16:16,741 --> 00:16:18,108
It's alright if you want to sleep more.

179
00:16:19,341 --> 00:16:20,108
Nah, i'm good.

180
00:16:25,174 --> 00:16:26,541
Hey, dear.

181
00:16:27,141 --> 00:16:28,874
Don't let my mom concern you.

182
00:16:29,341 --> 00:16:31,408
My mom cannot force me.

183
00:16:33,008 --> 00:16:34,541
But she's persistence.

184
00:16:35,774 --> 00:16:36,974
You're right.

185
00:16:38,341 --> 00:16:40,741
That's why the way we will talk to my mom...

186
00:16:41,008 --> 00:16:43,241
is going to be her daughter way.

187
00:16:43,808 --> 00:16:45,541
I'll take the role of...

188
00:16:45,541 --> 00:16:48,574
the little miss that whenever she needs anything, she has to get it right away.

189
00:16:49,174 --> 00:16:50,008
How's that?

190
00:16:51,474 --> 00:16:52,308
Like...

191
00:16:52,841 --> 00:16:59,408
if she wants me to go home, do some works, she has to let me date with you.

192
00:17:01,141 --> 00:17:02,241
If not?

193
00:17:02,708 --> 00:17:06,441
If not, I'll go back to be Lyla.

194
00:17:07,374 --> 00:17:11,608
Run away with you and never let her see me again.

195
00:17:21,608 --> 00:17:22,474
Lalin.

196
00:17:23,708 --> 00:17:24,974
Think about it carefully.

197
00:17:27,008 --> 00:17:29,541
I don't want you to upset your mother.

198
00:17:33,808 --> 00:17:35,841
She loves you very much.

199
00:17:38,208 --> 00:17:39,974
Perhaps.

200
00:17:42,008 --> 00:17:43,608
I have to prove myself.

201
00:17:45,408 --> 00:17:47,841
That I can take care of her only daughter.

202
00:17:48,841 --> 00:17:51,008
You don't have to prove anything.

203
00:17:51,674 --> 00:17:53,641
It's my life and I chose my way.

204
00:17:54,574 --> 00:17:56,808
I also know that I chose the right choice.

205
00:17:57,574 --> 00:17:59,141
- You sure? - Yeah.

206
00:17:59,441 --> 00:18:01,008
More than sure.

207
00:18:30,174 --> 00:18:35,108
[Miss you already. Wanna grab dinner tonight?]

208
00:18:39,808 --> 00:18:44,741
[I got a meeting but i'll rush to you when I finished.]

209
00:18:49,908 --> 00:18:51,808
G' morning, boss.

210
00:18:55,408 --> 00:18:58,241
Wow, you seems happy today.

211
00:18:58,541 --> 00:19:00,641
Like those who got a lovey-dovey.

212
00:19:00,974 --> 00:19:03,474
Boss, what lovey-dovey?

213
00:19:03,774 --> 00:19:06,241
Aiy don't have time for that kind of thing?

214
00:19:06,574 --> 00:19:09,741
I only got time for good news for you.

215
00:19:10,641 --> 00:19:11,774
Does this mean...

216
00:19:11,974 --> 00:19:13,674
You've got a lover, right?

217
00:19:13,674 --> 00:19:16,008
It's not that. Come on, boss.

218
00:19:16,408 --> 00:19:21,441
Good news is I found way that we can defeat your rival's company.

219
00:19:23,108 --> 00:19:23,974
How?

220
00:19:25,308 --> 00:19:26,241
It's Mr. Kevin.

221
00:19:26,608 --> 00:19:27,741
I found his weakness.

222
00:19:45,808 --> 00:19:46,674
Let's talk later.

223
00:19:46,808 --> 00:19:47,941
I have to leave now.

224
00:19:48,674 --> 00:19:49,808
I'll wait for your message.

225
00:19:50,041 --> 00:19:50,674
Got it.

226
00:20:15,941 --> 00:20:17,041
You're beautiful enough.

227
00:20:19,574 --> 00:20:20,674
Thank you.

228
00:20:22,308 --> 00:20:23,774
Miss Kratai, right?

229
00:20:24,741 --> 00:20:26,374
Yes. Do we know each other?

230
00:20:33,041 --> 00:20:34,441
You don't know me.

231
00:20:35,341 --> 00:20:36,574
But I know you.

232
00:20:37,474 --> 00:20:39,141
I know even your real job.

233
00:20:40,141 --> 00:20:41,208
So what?

234
00:20:42,441 --> 00:20:43,608
Got a job for me?

235
00:20:44,641 --> 00:20:46,574
But I only accept VIP's request.

236
00:20:48,474 --> 00:20:49,641
One Prosecco please.

237
00:20:51,941 --> 00:20:53,108
Your bar...

238
00:20:53,641 --> 00:20:56,208
is so nice. I really like the deco.

239
00:20:57,408 --> 00:21:00,408
If I want to launch the bar more, how much does it cost?

240
00:21:02,741 --> 00:21:05,241
A lot. No need to launch it more.

241
00:21:05,441 --> 00:21:07,674
Just try to keep what you have alive first.

242
00:21:08,208 --> 00:21:11,374
Come on. I just like this style.

243
00:21:11,374 --> 00:21:12,474
Have you slept?

244
00:21:14,774 --> 00:21:15,908
Yeah, just a lil bit.

245
00:21:17,041 --> 00:21:20,141
Before you wanna open more bars, just try to rest properly.

246
00:21:20,141 --> 00:21:21,108
Right.

247
00:21:27,008 --> 00:21:28,174
Here's your Prosecco.

248
00:21:35,841 --> 00:21:37,408
Your bar is full of customers, no?

249
00:21:42,474 --> 00:21:44,774
- Lady first. - Thank you.

250
00:21:47,008 --> 00:21:50,374
So you really think this through, about going back with Arisa.

251
00:21:50,541 --> 00:21:51,741
What about your mother?

252
00:21:52,741 --> 00:21:54,508
I'm dealing with those.

253
00:21:55,141 --> 00:21:56,308
No need to worry.

254
00:21:56,674 --> 00:21:57,741
I got this.

255
00:21:58,241 --> 00:22:02,441
I didn't worry about anything and I always support your love life.

256
00:22:02,741 --> 00:22:05,774
But I just concerned that you might got tricked.

257
00:22:06,008 --> 00:22:07,374
And you got no idea about that.

258
00:22:08,674 --> 00:22:10,041
What do you mean?

259
00:22:11,241 --> 00:22:12,308
Take a look at this.

260
00:22:21,808 --> 00:22:22,541
Here.

261
00:22:23,208 --> 00:22:26,208
I was doing my things at my friend's bar and met her with that girl.

262
00:22:26,941 --> 00:22:31,774
That girl is kinda hot, dressed in a sexy outfit and they talked so close. What do you think?

263
00:22:34,074 --> 00:22:35,641
You're overthinking.

264
00:22:36,408 --> 00:22:38,241
They're probably friends.

265
00:22:39,641 --> 00:22:42,408
It could be but if not?

266
00:22:42,741 --> 00:22:45,208
I don't know but I'm your friend.

267
00:22:45,941 --> 00:22:47,574
She's my suspect.

268
00:22:48,541 --> 00:22:50,841
Yeah. Thanks.

269
00:22:52,174 --> 00:22:53,608
But I think it's nothing.

270
00:22:54,374 --> 00:22:56,341
She'd told me if it's something.

271
00:22:57,174 --> 00:22:59,374
We promised, no more lie to each other.

272
00:23:00,574 --> 00:23:02,741
Right. It's up to you then.

273
00:23:02,741 --> 00:23:03,808
I'm just the messeger.

274
00:23:04,074 --> 00:23:06,508
